## Phase 1 - Tailscale + remote shell

```bash
curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh
sudo tailscale up --ssh        # --ssh lets you SSH in over the tailnet with no key management
sudo tailscale set --hostname box
```

Then on the Mac and phone: install Tailscale, sign into the same tailnet, confirm `tailscale status` lists `box`. MagicDNS gives you `box` as a hostname for free.

- iPhone shell client: **Blink Shell** (best mosh + Tailscale support) or Termius.
- Keep the box awake on lid-close: `sudo systemctl mask sleep.target suspend.target` (a laptop-as-server wants no suspend), or set it in your DE power settings. This is what makes "always on" true.

