## Phase 3 - PAI runtime on the box

```bash
# the crown jewels - clone from your private remote (see Backup/DR for setting this up)
git clone git@github.com:<you>/life-os.git ~/.claude      # or your chosen remote

cd ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE && bun install
cd ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE/Observability && bun install && bun run build   # next build → out/

# secrets - never committed; restore from password manager / OneDrive
cat > ~/.claude/.env <<'EOF'
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=...
TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS=...
EOF
chmod 600 ~/.claude/.env

# authenticate the CLI once interactively (over rc), then it persists
claude   # complete OAuth login, or export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in your shell profile
```

**Casing gotcha (confirmed on first box clone).** The canonical directory is `PAI/PULSE` (uppercase - that is what git tracks, what the launchd plist and `pulse.ts` use). macOS is case-insensitive so `Pulse` and `PULSE` resolve to the same place and the difference is invisible; Linux is case-sensitive and only `PULSE` exists. Every script, unit, and command must say `PULSE`. (Lesson learned the hard way: an earlier edit "corrected" `PULSE`→`Pulse`, which looked fine on the Mac and broke `bun install`/`manage.sh` on the box.)

