## Phase 4 - Services (systemd user units, ported from the launchd plists)

**These units now exist as version-controlled files** in `~/.claude/PAI/PULSE/linux/` (`pulse.service`, `pai-cadence-daily.{service,timer}`, `pai-cadence-weekly.{service,timer}`), and `manage.sh` installs them. So on the box the whole of Phase 4 is:

```bash
sudo loginctl enable-linger "$USER"        # CRITICAL: user services run at boot, no login needed
cd ~/.claude/PAI/PULSE
./manage.sh install                        # installs + starts pulse.service, verifies :31337
./linux/install-cadence.sh                 # installs the daily + weekly cadence timers
./manage.sh status && systemctl --user list-timers 'pai-cadence-*'
```

The unit definitions below are reference for what those installers write.

**`pulse.service`** (replaces `com.pai.pulse`, `KeepAlive` → `Restart=always`):
```ini
[Unit]
Description=PAI Pulse
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=simple
WorkingDirectory=%h/.claude/PAI/PULSE
ExecStart=%h/.bun/bin/bun run pulse.ts
Restart=always
RestartSec=30
Environment=HOME=%h
Environment=PATH=%h/.bun/bin:%h/.local/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
StandardOutput=append:%h/.claude/PAI/PULSE/logs/pulse-stdout.log
StandardError=append:%h/.claude/PAI/PULSE/logs/pulse-stderr.log

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

**`pai-cadence-daily.service` + `.timer`** (weekdays 06:30):
```ini
# pai-cadence-daily.service
[Service]
Type=oneshot
WorkingDirectory=%h/.claude/PAI/USER/Routines
ExecStart=%h/.bun/bin/bun %h/.claude/PAI/USER/Routines/run-cadence.ts daily
Environment=HOME=%h
Environment=PATH=%h/.bun/bin:%h/.local/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
```
```ini
# pai-cadence-daily.timer
[Timer]
OnCalendar=Mon..Fri 06:30
Persistent=true
[Install]
WantedBy=timers.target
```

**`pai-cadence-weekly.timer`** is identical with `ExecStart=... run-cadence.ts weekly` and `OnCalendar=Mon 07:00`.

`Persistent=true` is the systemd answer to "the box was asleep at 06:30" - it fires the missed run on wake. launchd did this implicitly; systemd needs it stated.

(Enable is handled by `manage.sh install` and `install-cadence.sh` above.)

**Do NOT port these** (Mac-only, useless headless): `com.pai.voice-server.plist`, the MenuBar app, `lib/imessage-send.ts`, `statusline-command.sh`. Voice output has nowhere to go on a headless box - see Phase 5.

