## Phase 5 - macOS-ism patches

The scan flagged these as the files with Darwin-only calls. The cadence runner and `Inference.ts` are clean and need nothing. The rest split into "patch" and "disable":

| File | Issue | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| `Pulse/start-pulse.sh`, `Pulse/manage.sh` | `launchctl`, `/opt/homebrew`, `stat -f` | Patch: `systemctl --user`, `$HOME/.bun`, `stat -c`. Add a `--linux` branch or fork the script. |
| `Pulse/VoiceServer/voice.ts` | `afplay`/`say` playback | DONE - `playAudio()` is now platform-gated: macOS plays via `afplay`, Linux silences. Set `PAI_AUDIO_PLAYER=<binary>` to re-enable (e.g. route box audio elsewhere). |
| `Pulse/lib/imessage-send.ts` | `osascript` iMessage | Disable. Mac-only API. Telegram covers outbound. |
| `Pulse/MenuBar/install.sh` | macOS menubar app | Skip entirely. |
| `statusline-command.sh` | `/opt/homebrew`, BSD `stat` | Patch only if you want the statusline over `rc`; low priority. |
| `Pulse/lib.ts` | likely `open`/`pbcopy` paths | Patch as encountered: `open`→`xdg-open`, `pbcopy`→`xclip -selection clipboard`. |

**Already patched (cross-platform, won't break the live Mac):** `manage.sh` and `start-pulse.sh` branch on `uname -s` (launchd on Darwin, `systemctl --user` on Linux), and all paths use the canonical `PULSE` casing. `voice.ts` playback is platform-gated and silent on the box. These changes are live in the repo; the Mac keeps using its Darwin paths unchanged.

General sed rule for the remaining low-priority ones (`statusline-command.sh`, `lib.ts`) when you hit them: BSD `stat -f` → GNU `stat -c`, `sed -i ''` → `sed -i`, `open` → `xdg-open`.

