## Phase 6 - Telegram: demote to notifications only

Telegram stays as a one-way digest channel (the cadence runner already posts to it over `fetch` - works on Linux as-is). Turn off the inbound side that was the source of this morning's friction:

- Stop relying on the Telegram task-runner as an interface. `rc` is the interface now.
- In `Pulse/modules/telegram.ts`, you can leave the bot polling for push, or disable inbound handling entirely. Recommendation: leave the outbound `sendMessage` path, gate or remove the `looksLikeTask` detached-runner block so inbound messages do not spawn agents. One channel for input (`rc`), one for push (Telegram).

